lence and service to the state, nation, and global society. These differences include but are not limited to race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, age, disabilities, and beliefs (e.g., health, sociological, religious, and socio-cultural barriers). These different groups will be represented in all facets of the College’s education and experiences such as our curricula content, faculty, student, staff and research representations to ensure a College climate that promotes the well-being and success of all.       Mission Statement      The mission of the Office of Diversity and Inclusion (ODI) is to promote increased recruitment, retention and advancement of diverse faculty, students and staff, and to oversee all diversity and inclusion activities involving UIC College of Pharmacy. The office also acts as a central resource for monitoring diversity and inclusion efforts and outcomes of the College’s Diversity Strategic Thinking and Planning committee.  The ODI believes that diversity adds value to intellectual development, academic discourse, patient care, research and service. The sharing of diverse ideas and perspectives is essential to the development of future leaders in health care to better serve our communities, and nation.  The ODI is committed to creating an environment that places importance on embracing, appreciating, and capitalizing on the rich perspectives and backgrounds of students, faculty and staff in other to accomplish a shared mission and vision.  Responsibilities of the office include:   Leadership of the college Diversity Strategic Thinking and Planning Committee  Implementation of the college’s framework to foster diversity and inclusion  Oversight of the creation of diversity and inclusion committees in the college  Liaison with the campus Office of Diversity.   Additional goals for the office include:   Increasing the diversity of candidate pools for faculty and staff positions,  Creating and expanding diversity-related professional-development opportunities for faculty, staff, and students  Promoting the creation of diversity-related student programs, and  Encouraging the recruitment and participation of underrepresented students in professional and graduate programs.   UIC Nondiscrimination Policy Statement https://policies.uic.edu/uic-policy-library/access-and-equity/nondiscrimination-policy-statement/      Institutional Diversity  Strategic Plan           Clara Okorie-Awé, Ph.D., Ed.D.  Associate Dean for Diversity and Inclusion, Director of Urban Pharmacy (UPHARM) Concentration, Director of the Urban Health Program (UHP), Clinical Associate Professor for Pharmacy Systems, Outcomes & Policy   833 South Wood Street, Suite 176,  MC 874,  Chicago,  Illinois  60612    Phone: 312-996-3516  Fax: 312-413-4119  Email: awe@uic.edu              Hitomi Oum, MEd  Associate Director for Diversity and Inclusion   833 South Wood Street, Suite 154C,  874,  Chicago,  Illinois  60612    Phone: 312-355-3535  Fax: 312-413-0106  Email: houm@uic.edu             About    Back to main content           Media Center    Events    By The Numbers    Our History    Chicago Campus    Rockford Campus     A Letter from the Rockford Dean      Strategic Plan    Diversity and Inclusion     Diversity Strategic Thinking and Planning (DSTP) Committee    Programs/Events    Community Engagement     Student-Community Engagement Reporting Form    Faculty-Community Engagement Reporting Form      Diversity Partners and College Resources    Annual Report 2018-2019    Travel Award    Upcoming Events & News                College of Pharmacy  UI Health                        UIC's seven health sciences colleges and health care delivery enterprise.       Administration    Office of the Dean    Student Affairs    Academic Affairs      Tools    my.UIC    Blackboard    E'Value    Directory    Intranet    Jobs    Photo Bin        Button Menu    Connect With Us    Book a Visit    Apply Now    Give         Contact   Chicago Campus  833 S. Wood St.